                                       'reading fluency, vocabulary, '
                                       'morphology and spelling. Results '
                                       'showed no significant\r\n'
                                       'improvement in passage comprehension, '
                                       'oral reading fluency, spelling or '
                                       'vocabulary from\r\n'
                                       'pre- to post-intervention testing. '
                                       'Statistically significant improvement '
                                       'was noted for The third study explored '
                                       'the effectiveness of a multi-component '
                                       'literacy intervention\r\n'
                                       'targeting the literacy skills of 10 '
                                       'mothers (M = 18;10) identified as '
                                       'low-achieving in reading\r\n'
                                       'comprehension. Using a '
                                       'pre-test/post-test research design '
                                       'with general comparison group (M\r\n'
                                       '= 18;6), the 26-session '
                                       'classroom-based intervention used '
                                       'same-language subtitled movies\r\n'
                                       'and a range of integrated literacy '
                                       'activities to target passage and word '
                                       'comprehension, oral\r\n'
                                       'reading fluency, vocabulary, '
                                       'morphology and spelling. Results '
                                       'showed no significant\r\n'
                                       'improvement in passage comprehension, '
                                       'oral reading fluency, spelling or '
                                       'vocabulary from\r\n'
                                       'pre- to post-intervention testing. '
                                       'Statistically significant improvement '
                                       'was noted for morphological awareness. '
                                       'When comparing results to a general '
                                       'comparison group, no\r\n'
                                       'significant improvement was detected '
                                       'in any area.\r\n'
                                       'The fourth study aimed to describe the '
                                       'language and development of 36 '
                                       'children of\r\n'
                                       'teenage mothers (M = 17 months). A '
                                       'range of standardised and '
                                       'parent-report assessment\r\n'
                                       'measures were used. Results varied '
                                       'considerably within the group on all '
                                       'measures. On\r\n'
                                       'clinician measures of language '
                                       'development, younger children '
                                       'performed more poorly than\r\n'
                                       'older children. Discrepancies were '
                                       'also observed between parent- and '
                                       'clinician-report\r\n'
                                       'measures. Parent measures primarily '
                                       'indicated children were performing '
                                       'within or at above\r\n'
                                       'average range in language and '
                                       'development. Conversely, '
                                       'clinician-report measures\r\n'
                                       'highlighted concerns with regards to '
                                       'children’s language development. In '
                                       'consideration of\r\n'
                                       'the risk profiles associated with '
                                       'teenage motherhood, the results '
                                       'suggested that these children\r\n'
                                       'may benefit from enriched language and '
                                       'literacy opportunities through quality '
                                       'shared reading\r\n'
                                       'interactions with their mothers.\r\n'
                                       'Given the home literacy environment '
                                       'was reported as lacking in enriched\r\n'
                                       'opportunities for literacy '
                                       'development, and children’s language '
                                       'development was identified\r\n'
                                       'as at-risk, the fifth study '
                                       'implemented a parent-targeted '
                                       'intervention to enrich the shared\r\n'
                                       'reading interactions experienced by 27 '
                                       'children of teenage mothers (M = '
                                       '19;6). Using a pretest/\r\n'
                                       'post-test research design mothers '
                                       'completed a seven week intervention '
                                       'based in the\r\n'
                                       'classroom, targeting a range of '
                                       'emergent literacy skills that they '
                                       'could utilise when reading\r\n'
                                       'with their children. A comparison '
                                       'cohort (n = 10; M = 18;3) was utilised '
                                       'to establish if\r\n'
                                       'assessed behaviours were commensurate '
                                       'with a similar population of teenage '
                                       'mothers.\r\n'
                                       'Assessments tracked changes in the '
                                       'type and frequency of mothers’ reading '
                                       'behaviours\r\n'
                                       'demonstrated during videoed shared '
                                       'reading interactions with their young '
                                       'children, as well as\r\n'
                                       'changes to aspects of the home '
                                       'literacy environment. A blinded, '
                                       'independent coder\r\n'
                                       'completed the data analysis. Results '
                                       'indicated significantly greater '
                                       'frequency of vocabulary, questioning '
                                       'and book/print features-focused '
                                       'reading behaviours from pre-test to '
                                       'post-test. No\r\n'
                                       'changes were observed in reading '
                                       'behaviours relating to letter/sound '
                                       'features.\r\n'
                                       'The sixth study provided an in-depth '
                                       'analysis of the quality and quantity '
                                       'of language\r\n'
                                       'used by mothers and children during '
                                       'the shared reading interactions '
                                       'collected in study five.\r\n'
                                       'Using a pre-test/post-test research '
                                       'design, language quality and quantity '
                                       'was measured during\r\n'
                                       'the shared reading interactions of 14 '
                                       'mother/child dyads (M = 19;9). '
                                       'Analysis examined\r\n'
                                       'MLU-m and total number of words and '
                                       'utterances used by mother and child, '
                                       'mother’s use of\r\n'
                                       'rare/sophisticated words, and '
                                       'children’s use of word classes. '
                                       'Discourse-level analysis was\r\n'
                                       'also completed, which examined five '
                                       'different types of conversational '
                                       'acts. Results\r\n'
                                       'demonstrated significant and '
                                       'meaningful changes in both language '
                                       'quality and quantity\r\n'
                                       'following the emergent literacy '
                                       'intervention. Changes at the discourse '
                                       'level were also\r\n'
                                       'observed.\r\n'
                                       'This thesis revealed that the language '
                                       'and literacy profiles of teenage '
                                       'mothers and\r\n'
                                       'their children are heterogeneous in '
                                       'nature, and may reflect a wide range '
                                       'of experiences and\r\n'
                                       'circumstances that existed before '
                                       'parenthood. This comprehensive '
                                       'collection of data is the\r\n'
                                       'first of its kind and provides '
                                       'detailed information on the language '
                                       'and literacy skills of this\r\n'
                                       'population. Despite the observed '
                                       'variability, it was determined that '
                                       'there is a need within this\r\n'
                                       'population for literacy support for '
                                       'both mothers and their children. This '
                                       'research also\r\n'
                                       'demonstrated differential changes in '
                                       'response to intervention when '
                                       'targeting the literacy\r\n'
                                       'skills of the mothers, and the way in '
                                       'which they share books with their '
                                       'children. The most\r\n'
                                       'positive changes were observed from '
                                       'the intervention that targeted shared '
                                       'book reading at\r\n'
                                       'both a behavioural and linguistic '
                                       'level. Analysis of the linguistic '
                                       'characteristics of shared\r\n'
                                       'reading interactions is a novel method '
                                       'of exploring response to intervention, '
                                       'and has not\r\n'
                                       'previously been examined in the '
                                       'literature.',
